    "minides": "India's most affordable and best-selling electric car — a completely refreshed Tiago EV with new dual-screen interior, auto LED headlamps, 360-degree camera, 6 airbags, 4 regen modes, 100 km in 18 min fast charging, and lifetime HV battery warranty on the 24 kWh pack.",
    "description": "The Tata Tiago EV received a full generational update in 2026, with a completely overhauled design — new dual-tone dashboard, two freestanding display units, a revised 2-spoke steering wheel with Tata.ev logo, new exterior colours, auto LED headlamps, and revised front and rear styling. It remains India's most accessible electric car, offered with 19.2 kWh (Smart/Pure+) and 24 kWh (Pure+/Creative+) battery packs. The 24 kWh battery offers 293 km MIDC range, 73.75 bhp, 114 Nm, and a lifetime high-voltage battery warranty — a segment first. DC fast charging now adds 100 km in just 18 minutes on the 24 kWh pack. Top variants add a 360-degree camera with Blind View Monitor, ESP with traction control, hill hold control, cruise control, rear AC vents, and 14-inch Hyperstyle alloys. No sunroof is offered on any variant. It competes with the MG Comet EV, Citroen eC3, and Hyundai Casper Electric."
  },
